<section id="general-information">
  <div class="main-information">
    <h1>Orthopedic Physiotherapy</h1>
    <img
      src="images/ourServicesData/specialisedData/ortho.jpg"
      loading="lazy"
      alt="Orthopedic Therapy"
    />
    <p>
      Orthopedic Physiotherapy is a specialized field that focuses on the
      injuries related to Bones, Ligaments, Tendons, Spinal discs, and Muscles.
      It does wonders in treating patients suffering from Musculoskeletal
      disorders at any age, whether a child, adult, or elderly. It includes a
      proper assessment of the conditions and rules out the exact cause of the
      problem and helps in managing them with proper Basic and Advance
      techniques.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our expert team of Physiotherapists not only treat all minor injuries that
      require short-term physiotherapies such as Simple Muscle strains, small
      fractures, or acute pains, but also all major injuries that require long
      term physiotherapies such as Rheumatoid arthritis, Severe disability, and
      excruciating pain conditions.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="information-with-points-1">
    <div class="information-1-image">
      <img
        src="images/ourServicesData/specialisedData/ortho-1.jpg"
        loading="lazy"
        alt="Orthopedic Therapy"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="information-1">
      <h5>
        Some of the Orthopedic conditions treated by our Physiotherapists are:
      </h5>
      <ul>
        <li>Ligament Strain</li>
        <li>Sprains</li>
        <li>Fractures</li>
        <li>Osteoarthritis</li>
        <li>Postural Problems</li>
        <li>Joint pains</li>
        <li>Low backaches</li>
        <li>Surgical Rehabilitation</li>
        <li>Ankylosing Spondylosis</li>
        <li>Spinal problems</li>
        <li>Scoliosis</li>
        <li>Fibromyalgia etc</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="information-3">
    <h5>How our Orthopedic Physiotherapists (OP) works?</h5>
    <ul>
      <li>
        OP works by Assessing their patients and examining them with the help of
        different clinical exams and investigations in order to make treatment
        plans.
      </li>
      <li>
        They help in treating patients suffering from different musculoskeletal
        problems with the help of various techniques and modalities.
      </li>
      <li>
        Various exercises are supervised by the therapist include:
        <ul>
          <li>Strengthening exercises</li>
          <li>Balancing exercises</li>
          <li>Mobility exercises</li>
          <li>Flexibility exercises</li>
          <li>Stretching</li>
          <li>Gait training exercises</li>
          <li>
            Manual techniques like Mobilization and Manipulations etc are done
            by the therapists that have shown to provide amazing results to the
            patients.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="information-with-point-2">
    <div class="information-2-image">
      <img
        src="images/ourServicesData/specialisedData/ortho-2.jpg"
        loading="lazy"
        alt="Occupational Therapy"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="information-2">
      <ul>
        <li>
          OP plans the exercise programs according to the patient&apos;s ability
          and conditions in order to help them get back to their normal daily
          functioning.
        </li>
        <li>
          They work on: Reducing pain, Increasing Strength and Flexibility,
          Maintaining correct Posture, Promoting the Healing process, Teaching
          proper Balance exercises, etc.
        </li>
        <li>
          They help you to get back to your normal activity pain-free and makes
          you stronger and independent in every way.
        </li>
        <li>
          Home exercise programs are designed by the therapists to help their
          patients return to their original healthy independent state.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
